SCC035-131130-
/O.CON.KCHS.TO.W.0007.000000T0000Z-200413T1130Z/
Dorchester SC-
720 AM EDT Mon Apr 13 2020

...A TORNADO WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 730 AM EDT FOR
DORCHESTER COUNTY...

At 718 AM EDT, a confirmed large and extremely dangerous tornado was
located over Givhans, moving northeast at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Damaging tornado.

SOURCE...Radar confirmed tornado.

IMPACT...Take cover now! Flying debris may be deadly to those caught
         without shelter. Mobile homes, other structures and
         vehicles could be damaged or destroyed.

Locations impacted include...
Summerville, Givhans Ferry State Park, Ridgeville, Givhans,
Knightsville and Jedburg.

This warning includes I-26 between mile markers 189 and 190.

PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS...

To repeat, a large, extremely dangerous and potentially deadly
tornado is on the ground. To protect your life, TAKE COVER NOW! Move
to a basement or an interior room on the lowest floor of a sturdy
building. Avoid windows. If you are outdoors, in a mobile home, or in
a vehicle, move to the closest substantial shelter and protect
yourself from flying debris.

Report damage directly to the Charleston National Weather Service at
1-888-383-2024 when it is safe to do so.

